item.title: Bouncy Castle
item.dc:creator: @dylan_0789 dylan_0789
item.description:
@dylan_0789 wrote:

I will go ahead and say that the Polygonal use was insufficient. In other words, you used a lot of unnecessary poly in which added no effect to the appearance. Why does the red have so much subdivision? it does not need to have sectors in between the ‘pillars’. Also, the way the Blue connects to the base of the model is incorrect, if you understand what I’m saying. The easiest way to fix this is to remove all those unused subdivisions of faces on the base and properly connecting the blue to it but really, its up to you how proper you want the wire frame to look. On a positive note, the overall structure is fairly well done. You are showing some progress from when you first started modeling, and no, nothing looks like a penis.

Read full topic
